 Park) - Jim Richards in a BMW 635 CSi.\n* 1986 Better Brakes 300 (Amaroo Park) - Tony Longhurst in a [[BMW E30|BMW 325i]] (2nd outright, 1st in Class B)\n* 1987 Hardie Irrigation 100 (Amaroo Park) - Jim Richards in a [[E30 M3|BMW M3]].\n* 1987 Pepsi 250 (Oran Park Raceway) - Jim Richards and Tony Longhurst  in a BMW M3.\n* [[1987 James Hardie 1000]] ([[Mount Panorama Circuit]]) - Jim Richards and Tony Longhurst  in a BMW M3 (4th outright, 1st in Class 2).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Australian auto racing teams]]\n[[Category:Sports teams in Sydney]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing, replaced: teams lead driver \u2192 team's lead driver (5)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JPS_Team_BMW"}
{"title_page": "NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship", "text_new": "{{ infobox football tournament\n| name                 = NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship\n| logo                 =  [[File:NCAA logo.svg|150px]]\n| caption              = \n| founded              = 1981\n| region               = \n| number of teams      = 6\n| current champions    = [[West Chester Golden Rams|West Chester]] (3)\n| most successful club = [[Bloomsburg Huskies|Bloomsburg]] (13)\n| broadcasters         = [[ESPNU]]\n| motto                = \n| website              = [https://www.ncaa.com/sports/fieldhockey/d2 NCAA.com]\n| current              = [[2019 NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship]]\n}}\n\nThe '''NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship''' is an annual single-elimination tournament conducted by the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] to determine the national champion of women's [[NCAA Division II|Division II]] collegiate [[field hockey]] in the [[United States]]. The tournament was held from 1981 and 1983, discontinued from 1984 and 1991, was re-instated in 1992, and has been held every year since.<ref>{{cite web|title=Division II Field Hockey Championship Results |url=http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/w_field_hockey_champs_records/2015/d2/D2.pdf|work=NCAA|publisher=NCAA.org|accessdate=September 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1984 and 1991, when the Division II tournament was not held, Division II teams competed in the [[NCAA Division III Field Hockey Championship]].\n\nThe most successful team are the [[Bloomsburg Huskies]], with thirteen titles. The [[West Chester Golden Rams]] are the current champions, winning their third national title against [[Saint Anselm Hawks|Saint Anselm]] in 2019.<ref>http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/w_field_hockey_champs_records/2013/d2/champ.pdf</ref> \n\nTeams from [[Pennsylvania]] have historically dominated the tournament. Aside from 1981, every year that small college championships have been conducted (AIAW: 1979 to 1981, NCAA: 1981 to 2012), one or more teams from Pennsylvania have played in either or both Division II and Division III national title games, winning 29 of 38 such games.\n\n==Format==\nCurrently, 6 teams compete in each national championship tournament. The first round is typically played on the campus of the higher-seeded teams. The semifinal and championship rounds are held at a pre-determined site. The 2019 finals were hosted by the [[Millersville University of Pennsylvania]].\n\n==Results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; width: 50%; text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=6|NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:5%;\"|Year \n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10%;\"|Site<br><small>(Host Team)</small>\n| style=\"width:1%;\" rowspan=\"5\"|\n! colspan=3|Final Match\n|-\n!width=14%|Champion \n!width=4%|Score \n!width=14%|Runner-up \n|-\n|1981<br>''[[1981 NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship|Details]]''\n| [[Misenheimer, North Carolina|Misenheimer, NC]]<br><small>([[Pfeiffer Falcons|Pfeiffer]])</small>\n| [[Pfeiffer Falcons|Pfeiffer]] \n| 5\u20133\n| [[Bentley Falcons|Bentley]]\n|-\n|1982<br>''[[1982 NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship|Details]]''\n| [[Bloomsburg, Pennsylvania|Bloomsburg, PA]]<br><small>([[Bloomsburg Huskies|Bloomsburg]])</small>\n| [[Lock Haven Bald Eagles|Lock Haven]] \n| 4\u20131\n| [[Bloomsburg Huskies|Bloomsburg]]\n|-\n|1983<br>''[[1983 NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship|Details]]''\n| [[Lock Haven, Pennsylvania|Lock Haven, PA]]<br><small>([[Lock Haven Bald Eagles|Lock Haven]])</small>\n| Bloomsburg\n| 1\u20130\n| Lock Haven\n|-\n|1984\u20131991\n|colspan=\"6\" | ''Not held\n|-\n|1992<br>''[[1992 NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship|Details]]''\n| Lock Haven, PA<br><small>(Lock Haven)</small>\n| style=\"width:1%;\" rowspan=\"55\"|\n| Lock Haven <small>(2)</small>\n| 3\u20131\n| Bloomsburg\n|-\n|1993<br>''[[1993 NCAA Division II Field Hockey Championship|Details]]''\n| Blooms